begin_memory_text: At the beginning of the conversation we talked about what parts of the country we were in and what the weather was like. Andrew said fall is his favorite season, and this is his favorite part of fall.
middle_memory_text: In the middle of the conversation we talked a bit about politics, but in more of an abstract way. We talked about local politics and how important it is for everyone to vote, regardless of their views.
end_memory_text: Toward the end of the conversation we talked about Halloween and whether or not we would be doing anything to celebrate. We also talked about our pets.
rest_of_day_open: Well, we're back to Monday. The kids are in virtual school and it continues to be a challenge, including this morning. Hopefully they will do better in the rest of the week, but the potential for that not to be the case is fairly high and looms over the rest of the week. I have a big doctor's appointment on Wednesday, so I am anxious about that and will feel better after it is over, as long as everything goes well.
critical_positive: I tried pretty hard to keep the conversation going. Luckily my conversation partner was responsive to my questions and would talk about things in great detail once prompted. We tried to find common ground and there was minimal overtalking. We were both listening to the other person's responses as well.
critical_negative: There was not really an equal exchange of either questions or information. When the conversation naturally ebbed, I felt like I had to ask the questions to keep it going. My partner would talk at length about something, but then wouldn't really follow up for my perspective or point of view.

begin_memory_text: We talked about the weather. It is cold and snowy where I am. She lives in California where things are a lot brighter and happier at the moment
middle_memory_text: We talked about politics. I mentioned how I had been doing some pamphlet drops, and my family had all completed their vote by mail ballots. We also talked about geocaching.
end_memory_text: We talked about pets. We both have dogs. We also discussed what our plans were for Halloween. She and her family are not really doing anything special like trick or treating.
rest_of_day_open: I see it going pretty well even if there may be some rough patches to deal with. I am making progress towards some goals when it comes to my health. I am probably going to go out and do some Geocaching with my dad at some point which should be a lot of fun.
critical_positive: We generally seemed to like each other well enough. The subjects we talked about were interesting. The discussion we got into about politics was particularly engaging. It was nice to hear from someone in a different state when it came how the elections were unfolding. That all went very well.
critical_negative: There were a bunch of pauses in the conversation that were kind of awkward. It did not flow very well at all. Some of that was my fault as I should have asked her more questions. She led the discussion, and sometimes ran out of things to talk about which resulted in gaps.
